SIMPLE: planting
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Planting
<hw>Plant"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
or operation of setting in the ground for propagation, as seeds, trees,
shrubs, etc.; the forming of plantations, as of trees; the carrying on
of plantations, as of sugar, coffee, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is planted; a plantation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Trees of righteousness, the <qex>planting</qex> of the Lord.</q>
<rj><qau>Isa. lxi. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The laying of the first courses
of stone in a foundation.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plantless</ent>⟦br⟧
